This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump in the Oval Office. He discusses his upcoming trip to Vietnam for a second summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un. He expresses optimism about the meeting and the potential for progress on denuclearization. The President also announces the signing of a new order to create the United States Space Force, emphasizing the importance of space as a warfighting domain. He and his administration officials discuss the significance of the Space Force and the need to protect American interests in space. The President also addresses trade talks with China, the recent terrorist attack in India, lawsuits against his executive order on border security, and the announcement of Bernie Sanders running for President.